snippet.textDisplay: Blue scares me. Like I have done purple, pink, magenta, red, and orange. I have relatively light brown hair, and I got platinum highlights a while back so I decided to start dying my hair some fun colors, so I started with purple like DARK purple and it showed up really well and I liked it so I then played around with reds and oranges and pinks as it faded and now my hair is pinkish, (more "rose gold" now that its faded), but blue always is one I cant bring myself to do, because for one I know I would have to fully bleach my hair to platinum, and I dont have thick hair so I imagine it will just fry from that, and I think even with that, everyone I know who has tried blue hair has it fade to green. Its never a pretty green, because I would actually be fine with some cool green hair, but its always like a "my hair hasn't been dyed in a while and is potentially dirty" kind of green. All the other colors, for the most part, I like the way they fade, the purple just fades and makes my hair look more pastel and then just like a toner it makes me a bit blonder, the red fades to a nice strawberry blonde, the orange makes my hair look a bit cooper, the pink fades to a rose gold tint (which my grandmother who doesn't like colored hair actually says she likes oddly). With blue I feel like you just really have to invest time and maintenance and with me I just let one color fade out and wear it until I put a new one in and so blue would really clash with that, also blue seems hard to switch colors with, for now most of the colors I go between work out pretty well together and fade somewhat natural-looking, with blue there is nothing natural about how it fades.

snippet.textDisplay: I went to a salon to get my hair dyed that silver color that was popular a few years back. It came out like a dark gray with patches of green in it. I was horrified, and told the stylist that it wasn't what I wanted. She tried to tell me that it would fade if I washed it. Like, yeah? Even these random patches of green? I ended up going straight home (after getting it bleached and dyed and paying a ridiculous amount of money) and using a color remover on it then dying blonde over it. Never going to a salon (at least not that one) to get my hair colored again. I went to a friend who bleached my hair for me about a year later and she did an amazing job. And it only cost me $10.
